📝 Five Golden Rules (Write these at the end of your notebook)

1. Never trust user input.


2. Patch vulnerabilities quickly.


3. Minimize the attack surface (remove unnecessary software/plugins).


4. Apply the Principle of Least Privilege.


5. Use Defense in Depth—no single security control is sufficient.



These five principles are applicable across almost every security topic you'll encounter, and they reflect the fundamental mindset your manager has been encouraging you to develop.
